  context={"endpoint"}
>

Deletes specific checkout records by identifier list. Use this when you have a known set of checkout IDs to remove without impacting other records.

**Prerequisites**
1. **AssetCheckoutIds** - Collect from [POST /api/v1.0/assets/checkouts/query/get](/docs/api/assets/get-asset-checkouts-by-query) or [POST /api/v1.0/assets/checkouts/transactions/query/get](/docs/api/assets/get-asset-checkout-transactions).

**Workflow Example**
1. Gather the checkout IDs that should be removed.
2. [DELETE /api/v1.0/assets/checkouts/ids/delete](/docs/api/assets/delete-asset-checkouts-by-ids) with the array of IDs.

**Minimal Required Fields**: request body array of checkout IDs.
